<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/quest.cgi?read=99" TARGET=_self>In general...</A> (SirKronos)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>not all npc's are going to give up quest information by just hailing them. this is a classic example. you found some one who said go to this other npc and asked about subject. If i go to the same other npc and hail them i get, whew its cold, and i dont get the quest information just handed to me because i didnt ask the key phrase to unlock the information., i would have toknow the key word to unlock that quest.. like what you found ask this npc about death. now he gives you an ear full cause you asked the proper key phrase to unlock that quest information. So in a round about response, no going around asking everyone if they have a quest for you will not not work. P.S becarfull what you post about quest so that you dont make it a spoiler. what you posted here is kind of a spoilier, I did not know about this quest but you have given me enough info here so now i can just go to the second npc and ask the phase and i will get some quest info and without having to talk to the first npc at all now. i suggest that everyone in the future when asking questions about quest they leave out names and key phases used to activate it.. so that it does not become a spoiler. Now i have no problem with some saying for this quest you need to go to npc 1 first .. but dont post info so that someone like me can go to npc 2 ask key phrase and get quest without haveing to go to npc 1 first.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="http://www.erols.com/silvera/Silver.jpg"></P>
